title: Google\Cloud\Speech\V2\PhraseSet
name: PhraseSet
description:
PhraseSet for biasing in speech recognition. A PhraseSet is used to provide "hints" to the speech recognizer to favor specific words and phrases in the results.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.speech.v2.PhraseSet

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data.uid
params.description: Output only. System-assigned unique identifier for the PhraseSet.

params.name: data.phrases
params.description: A list of word and phrases.

params.name: data.boost
params.description: Hint Boost. Positive value will increase the probability that a specific phrase will be recognized over other similar sounding phrases. The higher the boost, the higher the chance of false positive recognition as well. Valid boost values are between 0 (exclusive) and 20. We recommend using a binary search approach to finding the optimal value for your use case.
